WIKI markup is very simple and 'light'. You can create your own 'online' documents/man-pages in very easy way.

Here is a short introduction to wiki markup

http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Formatting#Inserting_symbols

After writtings of wiki, please, convert it to html man-pages, ie

<mva-classes.wiki>
1)  ./mediawiki2texi.py mva-classes.wiki mva-classes.info "MVA Classes" > mva-classes.texinfo
2)  makeinfo --html mva-classes.texinfo 
you can get simple README file (text file)
3) makeinfo mva-classes.texinfo

<mva-train.wiki>
1)  ./mediawiki2texi.py mva-train.wiki mva-train.info "MVA Training" > mva-train.texinfo
2)  makeinfo --html mva-train.texinfo
you can get simple README file (text file)
3) makeinfo mva-train.texinfo




